    "attributes": {
        "action": "Restrict the use of drones by police for the purpose of surveillance",
        "additional_details": "Unless there is an active crime or serious suspicion of threat to democracy, we believe the interference with the right to privacy cannot be justified on legal grounds, and that drones should not be used for surveillance under any other circumstances.",
        "background": "In accordance with Article 8 of the European Convention on Human Rights, police should not intrude on the private lives of our people via drone technology unless there is an active crime or serious suspicion of threat to democracy.",
